 functionals\nincluding about 50% of Hartree-Fock exchange. In contrast, in the case of\n[Fe(CO)$_6$]$^{2+}$, the failure is likely to be caused by the\nmulticonfigurational character of the ground state wave-function and no\nsuitable exchange and correlation functional has been identified.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Jun 2012 18:33:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
